\f1\b \cf0 Step 1 \'97 Hosting (today)
\f0\b0  Go to Vercel.com. Free tier is fine to start. Connect a GitHub account \'97 Vercel deploys directly from a repo.\

\f1\b Step 2 \'97 Build the page
\f0\b0  Open Claude Code in your terminal. Paste the instructions from the previous message. It will scaffold the Next.js project, build the page, and give you a folder ready to deploy.\

\f1\b Step 3 \'97 Deploy
\f0\b0  Push the folder to a GitHub repo. Connect that repo to Vercel. It auto-deploys in about 60 seconds and gives you a vercel.app URL immediately.\

\f1\b Step 4 \'97 Connect your domain
\f0\b0  In Vercel dashboard go to your project \uc0\u8594  Settings \u8594  Domains \u8594  add extractsignal.com. Vercel gives you two DNS records to add. Go to Namecheap \u8594  manage your domain \u8594  Advanced DNS \u8594  paste those records in. Propagation takes 10\'9630 minutes.\

\f1\b Step 5 \'97 Email
\f0\b0  Go to Cloudflare Email Routing (free) or Improvmx.com (free tier). Both let you forward {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:zach@extractsignal.com"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 zach@extractsignal.com}} to whatever personal inbox you already use. No email server needed.\
That's the full stack. Domain you have. Everything else is free until you have revenue. Total time to live site is under two hours if you move straight through it.\
