\f1\b \cf0 1 \'97 Start Google Workspace
\f0\b0  Go to workspace.google.com \uc0\u8594  click "Get started" \u8594  enter your business name (ExtractSignal) \u8594  number of employees (just you) \u8594  your existing personal Gmail as the recovery email \u8594  when asked about domain select "I have a domain" \u8594  type extractsignal.com \u8594  continue through billing \u8594  $6/month, cancel anytime.\

\f1\b 2 \'97 Verify domain ownership
\f0\b0  Google will give you a TXT record. It looks like: google-site-verification=xxxxxxxxxxxxx Go to Namecheap \uc0\u8594  Domain List \u8594  Manage \u8594  Advanced DNS \u8594  Add New Record \u8594  Type: TXT \u8594  Host: @ \u8594  Value: paste the code \u8594  Save. Back in Google click Verify. Takes 2\'965 minutes.\

\f1\b 3 \'97 Add MX records
\f0\b0  Google gives you 5 MX records to add. In Namecheap Advanced DNS delete any existing MX records first then add all five exactly as Google specifies. These are the ones that actually route email to Gmail.\

\f1\b 4 \'97 Finish Google setup
\f0\b0  Back in Google Workspace finish the wizard. Your inbox at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:zach@extractsignal.com"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 zach@extractsignal.com}} will be live within 30 minutes of the MX records saving.\

\f1\b 5 \'97 Access your email
